# Operation Scholars OS — Environment & Deployment Rules

---

## Environment Variables — Required Keys

All of the following must exist in `.env` (local) and in Vercel (all environments: production, preview, development).

```bash
# .env.example — commit this file with descriptions, never with values

# ─── DATABASE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase connection pooler (pgBouncer) — used by Prisma at runtime
# Format: postgresql://postgres.[project-ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1
DATABASE_URL=

# Supabase direct connection — used by Prisma for migrations only (port 5432, no pgbouncer)
# Format: postgresql://postgres.[project-ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
DIRECT_URL=

# ─── AUTH ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NextAuth secret — generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=

# NextAuth URL — full URL of deployment (no trailing slash)
# Local: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://scholars.quasarnova.net
NEXTAUTH_URL=

# ─── AI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Anthropic API key — from console.anthropic.com
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─── APP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment identifier — used for conditional logging
# Values: development | preview | production
NODE_ENV=
```

---

## Secrets Rules

- All secrets in environment variables. No exceptions.
- `.env` is in `.gitignore`. Never commit it.
- `.env.example` is committed with key names and descriptions. Never values.
- No secrets in `next.config.ts`, source files, or comments.
- No hardcoded API keys, database URLs, or passwords anywhere in the codebase.
- Rotate `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` immediately if it appears in any commit or log.

---

## Environment Variable Access Patterns

```typescript
// CORRECT — server-side only (API routes, lib files, server components)
const apiKey = process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
if (!apiKey) throw new Error('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is not set')

// CORRECT — exposing to client: NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix only, non-sensitive values only
// No NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables are needed for this application.
// Student data never flows to client-side environment variables.

// WRONG — never access server secrets in client components or browser context
// Never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ for API keys, database URLs, or auth secrets
```

