## Production Deploy Checklist

Never deploy to production without Daniel's explicit sign-off. When sign-off is given, verify:

- [ ] All 10 Phase 1 acceptance criteria pass on staging
- [ ] All environment variables set in Vercel production environment
- [ ] `prisma migrate deploy` run against production database (not `migrate dev`)
- [ ] No `console.log` statements containing student data
- [ ] `.env` not in repository
- [ ] `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` is production-specific (not shared with dev)
- [ ] De'marieya's owner account created with a secure initial password
- [ ] Seed data confirmed (2–3 anonymized test students)

---

## Migration in CI/CD

```bash
# Development — creates migration files and applies them
npx prisma migrate dev --name migration_name

# Production / CI — applies existing migration files only, no schema diff
npx prisma migrate deploy

# Never run `prisma migrate dev` against production
# Never run `prisma migrate reset` against production
```

---

## What Never Happens

- `typescript.ignoreBuildErrors: true` — never. Fix the type error.
- `eslint.ignoreDuringBuilds: true` — never. Fix the lint error.
- Secrets committed to the repository in any file
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix on any sensitive variable
- Deploying to production without owner sign-off
- Running `prisma migrate dev` or `prisma migrate reset` against the production database
- Sharing `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` across environments
